{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TRgaJQuboniaWsovs3uwZF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files with specific patterns. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. **Filenames**: `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.24.txt`\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens/underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match the main title in the text content\n\n2. **Recipe Mix**: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n   - Categories: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n   - Multi-word (2-5 words) and single-word titles\n   - MUST be different from the 105+ existing recipes listed\n\n3. **Pattern Requirements**:\n   - 5 files with OCR_CORRUPTION: Misrecognized characters (digits for letters, dotless i, hyphenation artifacts, garbage tokens)\n   - 3 files with NARRATIVE: 3-7 lines of prose cooking story/introduction before ingredient list\n   - 2 files with SIMPLE: Basic OCR noise (stray numbers, page headers, broken words)\n\n4. **File Length**: 15-60 lines\n\nLet me plan 10 recipes that don't exist in the provided list:\n\nEnglish recipes (6):\n1. Roasted Root Medley (SIMPLE)\n2. Creamy Mushroom Soup (CORRUPTION)\n3. Lemon Tart (NARRATIVE)\n4. Grilled Vegetables (SIMPLE)\n5. Tomato Risotto (CORRUPTION)\n6. Berry Fool (NARRATIVE)\n\nPolish recipes (4):\n1. Żabina w Syropie (CORRUPTION)\n2. Bigos Jesienno-Zimowy (NARRATIVE)\n3. Kluski Śląskie (CORRUPTION)\n4. Chleb Żytni ze Słonecznikiem (CORRUPTION)\n\n\n5. Piernik Tradycyjny (NARRATIVE)\n\nI need to verify these titles don't overlap with the existing 105+ recipes in the provided list. Checking against what's already there, I'll refine my selections to ensure complete uniqueness—titles like \"Roasted Beet and Carrot Medley,\" \"Creamy Mushroom and Barley Soup,\" \"Lemon Custard Tart,\" and \"Grilled Zucchini with Herbs\" offer enough specificity to avoid duplication while maintaining realistic recipe naming conventions. . **Lemon Custard Tart** (English) - NARRATIVE\n4. **Grilled Zucchini with Herbs** (English) - SIMPLE\n5. **Tomato and Basil Risotto** (English) - CORRUPTION\n6. **Raspberry and White Chocolate Fool** (English) - NARRATIVE\n7. **Żabina w Syropie Cukrowym** (Polish) - CORRUPTION\n8. **Bigos Łowiecko-Zimowy** (Polish) - NARRATIVE\n9. **Kluski Gościnne z Makiem** (Polish) - CORRUPTION\n10. **Chleb Żytni ze Słonecznikiem** (Polish) - CORRUPTION\n\nNow I'll generate the actual files with appropriate OCR patterns. For SIMPLE entries, I'll use basic OCR noise like character substitutions and spacing errors.\n\nFor CORRUPTION entries, I'll introduce character replacements like '1' replacing 'l', dotless 'ı' characters, hyphenation breaks mid-word, and random garbage tokens scattered throughout both Polish and English recipes.\n\nFor NARRATIVE entries, I'll include 3-7 lines of prose describing the dish's origins or cooking philosophy before moving into the structured ingredient list.\n\nI'm creating 10 files now:\n\nFile 1: Roasted Beet and Carrot Medley (SIMPLE, 25 lines)\nFile 2: Creamy Mushroom and Barley Soup (CORRUPTION, 45 lines)\nFile 3: Lemon Custard Tart (NARRATIVE, 40 lines)\nFile 4: Grilled Zucchini with Herbs (SIMPLE, 20 lines)\nFile 5: Tomato and Basil Risotto (CORRUPTION, 50 lines)\nFile 6: Raspberry and White Chocolate Fool (NARRATIVE, 35 lines)\nFile 7: Żabina w Syropie Cukrowym (CORRUPTION, 30 lines)\nFile 8: Bigos Łowiecko-Zimowy (NARRATIVE, 45 lines)\nFile 9: Kluski Gościnne z Makiem (CORRUPTION, 25 lines)\nFile 10: Chleb Żytni ze Słonecznikiem (CORRUPTION, 35 lines)\n\nNow generating each file with appropriate OCR artifacts and formatting patterns.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89017,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_