{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01C9xjKAXFcuRiz8KScs6yBS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LQLUFBKBSaW9bAN3cEqnQq","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lemon Custard Tart.generated.24.txt","content":"LEMON CUSTARD TART\n\nThis elegant tart is a celebration of spring brightness and smooth,\nsilky custard. The recipe comes from a small patisserie in Lyon where\nmaster baker Henri Marchand has been perfecting this dessert for over\nthirty years. The secret lies in the balance between sharp lemon zest\nand the delicate sweetness of the custard filling. Whether served\nat an afternoon tea or as a refined dinner finale, this tart brings\na touch of French sophistication to any table.\n\nServes 8 | Prep: 25 min | Chill: 2 hours | Cook: 35 min\n\nFOR THE PASTRY SHELL:\n\n250g all-purpose flour\n100g cold butter, cubed\n1 egg yolk\n1 tbsp sugar\n1/2 tsp salt\n3-4 tbsp ice water\n\nFOR THE CUSTARD FILLING:\n\n5 large egg yolks\n100g sugar\nZest of 4 lemons\n100ml fresh lemon juice (about 3-4 lemons)\n150ml heavy cream\n50g butter\nPinch of salt\n\nINSTRUCTIONS FOR PASTRY:\n\n1. Combine flour, sugar, and salt in food processor.\n2. Add cold butter and pulse until mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs.\n3. Add egg yolk and ice water, pulse until dough just comes together.\n4. Wrap in plastic and chill 1 hour.\n5. Roll out and press into 10-inch tart pan. Prick with fork.\n6. Chill 30 minutes. Bake at 375°F for 12-15 minutes until light\n   golden. Cool slightly.\n\nFOR THE CUSTARD:\n\n1. Whisk egg yolks with sugar until pale and thick, about 3 minutes.\n2. Stir in lemon zest and juice.\n3. Place mixture over double boiler and cook, whisking constantly,\n   until thickened (about 10 minutes). Should coat the back of a spoon.\n4. Remove from heat and stir in butter and cream until smooth.\n5. Pass through fine sieve. Pour into cooled tart shell.\n6. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.\n\nGarnish with candied lemon slices if desired."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":684,"cache_read_input_tokens":106493,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":684},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0fe839c1-c33d-4f82-850c-3b2e6f8def22","uuid":"27ec01e8-673b-4abe-81aa-a1310573553d"}
