{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01PAwhjV8dqvqXwbebZXmbTU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015cVkA2CtivxBh9nHM2jVy4","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Raspberry and White Chocolate Fool.generated.24.txt","content":"RASPBERRY AND WHITE CHOCOLATE FOOL\n\nThis classic British dessert is a study in simplicity and elegance. The\n\"fool\" tradition dates back centuries, when fresh berries were folded into\nthick cream or custard to create a light, cloud-like confection. This modern\ninterpretation marries the tartness of fresh raspberries with the buttery\nsweetness of white chocolate, creating a dessert that feels both indulgent\nand refreshingly delicate. Perfect served in individual glasses for a\nrestaurant-worthy presentation at home.\n\nServes 4-6 | Prep: 20 min | Chill: 1 hour\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n\n300g fresh raspberries (or frozen, thawed)\n100g white chocolate, chopped\n300ml heavy cream, cold\n2 tbsp icing sugar\n1 tbsp raspberry liqueur (optional)\n1 tsp vanilla extract\nZest of 1/2 lemon\nPinch of salt\nFresh mint leaves for garnish\nAdditional raspberries for topping\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Gently warm white chocolate with 2 tbsp of the heavy cream in a\n   double boiler or microwave (in 30-second bursts, stirring between).\n   Allow to cool slightly.\n\n2. In a separate bowl, whip remaining cold cream with icing sugar and\n   vanilla extract until soft peaks form.\n\n3. Fold cooled white chocolate mixture gently into whipped cream,\n   being careful not to deflate the cream.\n\n4. Reserve 8-10 raspberries for garnish. Gently crush remaining\n   raspberries with a fork. Fold in lemon zest and salt. If using\n   liqueur, stir it in with the raspberries.\n\n5. Layer the fool in individual serving glasses: alternate layers of\n   white chocolate cream with raspberry mixture, ending with a swirl\n   of cream on top.\n\n6. Chill for at least 1 hour. Just before serving, top with reserved\n   fresh raspberries and a small mint leaf.\n\nSERVING SUGGESTION: Pair with buttery shortbread biscuits or ladyfinger cookies.\nA dessert wine like Moscato d'Asti complements beautifully."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":758,"cache_read_input_tokens":108458,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":758},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0fe839c1-c33d-4f82-850c-3b2e6f8def22","uuid":"a8c05df0-8488-4884-88f8-db4529862520"}
